              <div id="section-header">
               <h1>
                Welcome to the Orange County Sheriff's Office
               </h1>
               <h4>
                We are pledged to protect, respect and assist you in many ways. My office provides you with information, helps you file a report, request records, report a crime, find a location, or ask a question.
               </h4>
               <div class="content-edit">
               </div>
              </div>
             </div>

          <div class="DnnModule DnnModule-XModPro DnnModule-431">
           <a name="431">
           </a>
           <div class="Container-H1">
            <!--Container Title-->
            <div class="dnntitle">
             <h1>
              <span class="title-H1" id="dnn_ctr431_dnnTITLE_titleLabel">
               Get Started
              </span>
             </h1>
            </div>
            <!--Container Title End-->
            <!--Container Content-->
            <div class="contentmain">
             <div class="contentpane" id="dnn_ctr431_ContentPane">
              <!-- Start_Module_431 -->
              <div class="DNNModuleContent ModXModProC" id="dnn_ctr431_ModuleContent">
               <div class="container">
                <div class="row front-tiles">
                 <div class="col-xs-12 col-sm-6 col-md-4 col-lg-4">
                  <div class="inner-col">
                   <h3>
                    Online Report Filing
                   </h3>
                   <p>
                    The OCSO Reporting System allows you to submit a non-emergency report. You can report the following incidents: Lost Property, Identity Theft, License Plate Lost/Stolen, Vehicle Burglary, Harassing Phone Calls and Vandalism.
                   </p>
                   <a href="/Crime-Information/File-Police-Report">
                    Read More
                   </a>
                   <br/>
                   <div class="content-edit">
                   </div>
                  </div>
                 </div>
                 <div class="col-xs-12 col-sm-6 col-md-4 col-lg-4">
                  <div class="inner-col">
                   <h3>
                    Requests for Public Records
                   </h3>
                   <p>
                    The Records/Identification Section is open from 8:00 a.m. until 5:00 p.m., Monday through Friday. Public Records request are accepted in person, via mail, phone request and email.
                   </p>
                   <a href="/Services/Administrative-Services/Support-Services-Division/Records-Identification-Section">
                    Read More
                   </a>
                   <br/>
                   <div class="content-edit">
                   </div>
                  </div>
                 </div>
                 <div class="col-xs-12 col-sm-6 col-md-4 col-lg-4">
                  <div class="inner-col">
                   <h3>
                    Crime Prevention and Community Relations
                   </h3>
                   <p>
                    Staffed by state certified Crime Prevention Specialists, the Orange County Sheriffs Office Crime Prevention Squad is committed to the task of stopping a crime before it can occur.
                   </p>
                   <a href="/Crime-Information/Crime-Prevention">
                    Read More
                   </a>
                   <br/>
                   <div class="content-edit">
                   </div>
                  </div>
                 </div>
                 <div class="col-xs-12 col-sm-6 col-md-4 col-lg-4">
                  <div class="inner-col">
                   <h3>
                    Directory of Services
                   </h3>
                   <p>
                    In this section, you will find a listing of contact information for various services in our county along with frequently requested phone numbers.
                   </p>
                   <a href="/Contact/Agency-Directory">
                    Read More
                   </a>
                   <br/>
                   <div class="content-edit">
                   </div>
                  </div>
                 </div>
                 <div class="col-xs-12 col-sm-6 col-md-4 col-lg-4">
                  <div class="inner-col">
                   <h3>
                    Community Events &amp; Programs
                   </h3>
                   <p>
                    Throughout the year the Sheriff's Office and its employees participate in or host a myriad of functions and special events. Many of these activities benefit special causes or people in need.
                   </p>
                   <a href="https://www.ocso.com/The-Daily-Briefing">
                    Read More
                   </a>
                   <br/>
                   <div class="content-edit">
                   </div>
                  </div>
                 </div>
                 <div class="col-xs-12 col-sm-6 col-md-4 col-lg-4">
                  <div class="inner-col">
                   <h3>
                    Employment Opportunities
                   </h3>
                   <p>
                    Whether you are seeking a position as a sworn deputy sheriff or looking for a job in one of our civilian support positions, the Orange County Sheriff's Office offers excellence in training and opportunity.
                   </p>
                   <a href="/Careers/Employment-Information">
                    Read More
                   </a>
                   <br/>
                   <div class="content-edit">
                   </div>
                  </div>
                 </div>
                </div>
               </div>
               <div class="content-new">
               </div>
              </div>
              <!-- End_Module_431 -->

                   <p>

Sheriff Demings is working closely with Orange County leaders to ensure Public Safety.  Review the following link and continue to follow news reports for the latest weather reports.

                 <div class="col-xs-12 col-sm-12 col-md-12 col-lg-12">
                  <h1>
                   OCSO in Action
                  </h1>
                  <h4>
                   Making a Difference ... Keeping Motorists Safe
                  </h4>
                  <div class="inner-content">
                   <p>
                    <iframe align="right" frameborder="0" height="281" scrolling="no" src="https://player.vimeo.com/video/273764168" width="500">
                    </iframe>
                   </p>
                   <p>
                    During the 2018 Click it or Ticket Campaign, Orange County Sheriff's Deputies ticketed 810 motorists for not wearing a seatbelt. Additionally, 39 motorists were ticketed for failure to place their young children in proper car seat or booster and 54 motorists received tickets for children between the ages of 6 and 17 not wearing a seatbelt.
                   </p>
                   <p>
                    Proper seatbelts and car seats saves lives. Occupants not wearing a seatbelt are more likely tosustain serious injury. It just takes a minute to make sure you and your passengers are secured.
                   </p>
                  </div>
                 </div>
                 <div class="col-xs-12 col-sm-12 col-md-12 col-lg-12 content-edit">
                 </div>
                 <div class="col-xs-12 col-sm-12 col-md-12 col-lg-12">
                  <h1>
                   OCSO in Action
                  </h1>
                  <h4>
                   Making a Difference ... Busting Drug Dealers
                  </h4>
                  <div class="inner-content">
                   <p>
                    <iframe align="right" allowfullscreen="" frameborder="0" height="281" mozallowfullscreen="" scrolling="no" src="https://player.vimeo.com/video/271517898" webkitallowfullscreen="" width="500">
                    </iframe>
                    The Orange County Sheriff's Office Narcotics Squad is out on the streets every day trying to bust drug dealers. This is a critical part of controlling the opioid crisis in Central Florida. So far this year, 215 arrests have been made. That's a 16% increase over last year. Fewer drug dealers helps keep neighborhoods safe.
                   </p>
                   <p>
                    To report a tip, call Crimeline at 1-800-423-TIPS (8477)
                   </p>
